"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-08-08-Nanjing-exhibition-showcases-relics-from-ancient-Greek-Olympics-1vTrvb4qha0-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  CGTN  Copied  The Paris Summer Games are in full swing, and the Nanjing Museum in east China's Jiangsu Province is offering a captivating glimpse into the origins of the Olympic spirit with its exhibition, \\\"The Glory of the Aegean Sea: An Exploration of Ancient Greek Civilization.\\\" Featuring artifacts such as bronze discuses, oil containers, and tripodal cauldrons, this exhibit brings the ancient Greek Olympics to life, allowing visitors to explore the rich cultural heritage of Greece some 3,000 years ago. The show runs until October 20th, celebrating the connection between past and present Olympic traditions.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"